(2, 'Using the T2 Project Dashboard', '<h3 style=\"line-height: 1;\"><b><font color=\"#ff9c00\" style=\"\">The Dashboard</font></b></h3><blockquote style=\"line-height: 1;\"><p>The Dashboard will be the first screen you are presented with when logging into the T2 Project Dashboard. Here you will find a number of module to keep you up to date with the latest news on your projects.</p></blockquote><p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><b><br></b></p><ol><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><b>Project Timeline: </b>The project timeline is where you will see a feed of latest notifications from all projects that you are currently assigned to<br></li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><b>Events: </b>Any events (Project related) currently added to your calendar will show here</li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><b>Sticky Notes: </b>Sticky notes are an area for you to write private notes or reminders (<i>To save your screens from Post-It notes!</i>)</li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><b>Clock In / Out: </b>The clock in feature helps to show project managers who is available and or working today - this will help project managers know which members of the team are available to work on projects, whether in the studio, working from home or part of an external team</li></ol><p><img src=\"http://team.t2ds.co.uk/assets/images/articles/Dashboard-Guide/01.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" class=\"mCS_img_loaded\"><br></p><p><br></p><h3 style=\"line-height: 1;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\"><font color=\"#ff9c00\" style=\"\">List of Projects</font></span></h3><blockquote style=\"line-height: 1;\">The List of Projects (All Projects) is where you will have access to the details of all projects that you have been currently assigned to. While projects are in production, the project status is listed as <b>Open</b>&nbsp;and they show in this list. Once a project has been completed and signed off the project status will be marked as <b>Completed</b>&nbsp;by a project manager or administrator and will be hidden from view.&nbsp;</blockquote><p style=\"line-height: 1;\"><br></p><ol><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><b>Project Title: </b>This is the title of the project. Click this title to see more details for this project<br></li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Deadline: </span>This is the overall deadline agreed with the client that the project will be completed</li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Progress:</span> The current progress is shown by calculating how many tasks are currently completed within the project when compared with any outstanding tasks</li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Project ID:&nbsp;</span>The Project ID corresponds to the project number used in the project folder system</li></ol><p><img src=\"http://team.t2ds.co.uk/assets/images/articles/Dashboard-Guide/02.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" class=\"mCS_img_loaded\"><br></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\"><br></span></p><h3><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\"><font color=\"#ff9c00\" style=\"\">Project Details</font></span></h3><blockquote style=\"line-height: 1;\">The project details page is where you will find all the information that you need to complete any work on a given project. Each project contains a set of tasks that once complete will satisfy all the requirements agreed with the client. The project details page is broken up into 8 separate tabs to help you navigate around the information as and when you need it. The first of these is the <b>Overview</b> tab. Here you will find a summary of the project along with an overview of current progress and updates.&nbsp;</blockquote><p style=\"line-height: 1;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\"><br></span></p><ol><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Timer Button:&nbsp;</span>This is the easiest way to track your time on a project. Once you click the Start timer button, the timer will be turned on. When you want to stop tracking the time you have to click on the Stop timer button. Once the time has been stopped you will be prompted to assign this time to a task in the project and this will be automatically logged and tracked within the project - along with the notes you provide summarising the work completed.</li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Project Progression:&nbsp;</span>The project progression chart represents the total progression of the project. You can also see the project deadline information inside this section</li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Task Status:&nbsp;</span>You can see the total tasks status of the project from the chart.&nbsp;</li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Activity Timeline:&nbsp;</span>Activity timeline represents the project history.&nbsp;</li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Project Members: </span>Here you can see which team members are involved in the project from start to end. Great for knowing who you will be collaborating with on tasks throughout the life of the job.</li></ol><p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><br></p><p><img src=\"http://team.t2ds.co.uk/assets/images/articles/Dashboard-Guide/03.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" class=\"mCS_img_loaded\"><br></p><h3><b style=\"\"><font color=\"#ff9c00\" style=\"\">Tasks</font></b></h3><h3><blockquote style=\"font-size: 13px; line-height: 1;\">The tasks page&nbsp;is where you can see created tasks that make up a project. Once you begin working on a task, you should move the card from <b>To Do</b> to <b>In Progress </b>(<i>Don\'t forget to start your timer too!</i>). All task cards remain visible to all members added to the project, however you can use some handy filtering features to keep the focus on your own tasks.&nbsp;</blockquote><p style=\"font-size: 13px; line-height: 1;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\"><br></span></p><ol style=\"font-size: 13px;\"><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Moving Cards:&nbsp;</span>To move a task card from one list to another is as easy as clicking and dragging the card. Once you move the card to a new list the status of that task and also add a notification to all users in the <b>Activity timeline</b></li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Assigned To Filter:&nbsp;</span>Using the <b>- Assigned To - </b>filter will let you select your own name from the list of users. This will hide all cards that are not currently assigned to you</li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">View Task Details:&nbsp;</span>To view more details on a given task, simply click the title to open the Task info popup&nbsp;</li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Commenting on cards:&nbsp;</span>You can comment on cards and add attachments for other users to see. These comments will also be received by email notification&nbsp;</li></ol><p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><br></p></h3><p><img src=\"http://team.t2ds.co.uk/assets/images/articles/Dashboard-Guide/04.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" class=\"mCS_img_loaded\"><br></p><h3 style=\"font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\"><font color=\"#ff9c00\">Task card details</font></span></h3><h3 style=\"font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><blockquote style=\"font-size: 13px; line-height: 1;\">Each task can be expanded to view more details on the requirements for the specified task. This may include any extra information regarding the task that you may need to know, the deadline to complete the task and and collaborators that you may be working alongside to receive or pass assets or information between tasks.</blockquote><p style=\"font-size: 13px; line-height: 1;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\"><br></span></p><ol style=\"font-size: 13px;\"><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Title &amp; Description: </span>The task title and description areas let project managers highlight any additional task specific information that may not be contained within the project overview</li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Milestones: </span>The milestones are defined at the start of the project and help to categorise tasks around any client specific dates or key deadlines throughout the project</li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Start Date &amp; Deadline:&nbsp;</span>This is the date that the task can be started and deadline to have the current task completed by.&nbsp;</li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Collaborators:&nbsp;</span>Collaborators show you which team members you will be working alongside for the current task. In the example below the collaborator is a 3D artist that will be supplying the CGI images to complete the house type artwork.</li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Remaining Duration (Hours):&nbsp;</span>The remaining duration begins as an agreed timescale that the current task will take to be completed. Once time has been logged using the <b>Start timer </b>button this will automatically be deducted from the remaining</li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Checklists:&nbsp;</span>Checklists can be created and updated to keep track of sub-tasks or additional steps required</li></ol></h3><h3><img src=\"http://team.t2ds.co.uk/assets/images/articles/Dashboard-Guide/05.jpg\" style=\"width: 50%;\" class=\"mCS_img_loaded\"><b><u><br></u></b></h3><h3><b><font color=\"#ff9c00\" style=\"\">Milestones</font></b></h3><blockquote><span style=\"background-color: rgba(242, 242, 242, 0.42);\">Milestones can be used to define interim deadlines within a project that a collection of tasks may need to be completed by. This helps to organise tasks to minimise any holdups during the project process. The milestones are visualised on the Gantt chart view.</span></blockquote><p><img src=\"http://team.t2ds.co.uk/assets/images/articles/Dashboard-Guide/06.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" class=\"mCS_img_loaded\"><br></p><h3><b><font color=\"#ff9c00\" style=\"\">Gantt Chart</font></b></h3><blockquote>The Gantt chart plots the duration of all tasks within a current project. This will allow project managers to view all the tasks at once (grouped by milestone) and identify any potential bottlenecks in the flow of information or assets.&nbsp;</blockquote><p><img src=\"http://team.t2ds.co.uk/assets/images/articles/Dashboard-Guide/07.jpg\" class=\"mCS_img_loaded\" style=\"width: 100%;\"><br></p><h3><b><font color=\"#ff9c00\">Files &amp; Comments</font></b></h3><blockquote>The files and comments tabs can be use to add project specific files or project specific comments for all users to see. Examples of this would be to upload the latest CAD to the <b>Files </b>tab for all external teams to download or a project manager using the <b>comments </b>tab to notify all users that a project has been put on hold by the</blockquote><p><img src=\"http://team.t2ds.co.uk/assets/images/articles/Dashboard-Guide/08.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" class=\"mCS_img_loaded\"><br></p><h3><b><font color=\"#ff9c00\">Timesheet</font></b></h3><blockquote>Timesheets track all of the logged hours for all users and all tasks in each project. It is important to accurately track your time using the start timer function as this will minimise the amount of admin required to get an accurate track of the total time spent on a project. Once a project has been completed, the timesheets can be use to generate reports to calculate accurate invoices calculate the success of each project.</blockquote><p><img src=\"http://team.t2ds.co.uk/assets/images/articles/Dashboard-Guide/09.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" class=\"mCS_img_loaded\"><br></p><h3><font color=\"#ff9c00\"><b style=\"font-family: inherit;\">Project Critique</b><br></font></h3><blockquote><span style=\"background-color: rgba(242, 242, 242, 0.42);\">The Project Crit section allows a project manager to add some feedback for the team on the completion of each project. This could be some excellent client feedback or comments, a technique or method that worked particularly well or some constructive criticism on an area that can be improved for the next project with this client.</span></blockquote><h3><b><font color=\"#ff9c00\" style=\"\">Calendar</font></b></h3><blockquote>The Calendar is the area that you can use to see all of the tasks that you have been assigned for the upcoming week. Tasks from all projects will show up here and the calendar can be used to review the current workload for the upcoming week. Project managers are able to see tasks for all users at once however to keep the calendar easier to user individual team members have a calendar filtered to tasks of the following types: <b>Assigned Tasks</b> and <b>Collaborator Tasks. </b>Clicking on the task title will open the task details popup window.</blockquote><p><br></p><ol><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Assigned Tasks:&nbsp;</span>Assigned tasks are tasks that have been directly assigned to you to complete. The tasks stretches from start to end date as indicated on the task details.&nbsp;</li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Collaborator Tasks:&nbsp;</span>Collaborator tasks are tasks that you have been added as a collaborator. This may mean that you need to provide some information to another team member or receive some information from a team member to complete one of your assigned tasks.&nbsp;</li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Colour Key:&nbsp;</span>Tasks on the calendar are colour coded as follows: <b>Grey</b>&nbsp;= Tasks to be completed <b style=\"color: rgb(247, 173, 107);\">Orange</b> = Tasks to be completed with an imminent deadline<b style=\"color: rgb(247, 173, 107);\">&nbsp;</b><font color=\"#6ba54a\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Green</font>&nbsp;= Tasks completed that require internal or external signoff&nbsp;<b style=\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\">Red&nbsp;</b>= Tasks that are not completed and have missed the deadline</li></ol><p><img src=\"http://team.t2ds.co.uk/assets/images/articles/Dashboard-Guide/10.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\" class=\"mCS_img_loaded\"></p><h3 style=\"font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\"><font color=\"#ff9c00\">Questions &amp; Feedback</font></span></h3><blockquote style=\"font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">If you have any further questions on how to use the T2 Project Dashboard, find any issues while using the system or have any feedback on how things could be improved - feel free to contact Tom Trembling either in the studio or by emailing tom.trembling@t2ds.com</blockquote>', 8, 1, '2019-01-30 15:57:50', 'active', 'a:0:{}', 27, 0),
