(23, '4286-00', 'Upton Place Brochure and wall board changes', 'To update the master A0 wall board with the latest floor plan changes and the brochure to reflect the following changes: \n \n• Ground floor layout, please change the AH plots to 167 and 168. Please refer to drawing attached for reference \n• Remove the AH reference on key of page 3\n• Plot 167 on the ground floor is a Sywell and 168 is a Everdon just like the first floor. These floor plans will need adding on page 3 or 4 \n• There’s no sliding doors to the lounge and bedroom on the ground floor of the Blisworth, Barnwell and Wansford house type. Please change to the attached doscument\n• The ‘7 styles to choose from’ will have to change to ‘9 styles…’ once the Sywell and Everdon is added to this page\n• On page 5, the first floor plan, plot 155 is in a grey  colour which represent AH when it should be olive green colour just like the Blisworth house type from page 4\n• There’s no sliding doors to the lounges and bedrooms to the Barnwell and Wansford house type on page 6 – please see attached for reference\n• On page 6, please add ‘balcony’ annotation outside the lounge/dining area to the Buckby house type \n• Page 7 and 8, there’s no sliding doors to lounges and bedrooms to the Brixworth, Ecton, Gayton and Holcot house type\n• Page 10, the third floor plan, plot 145 and 147 is now AH so please remove colours and make grey. \n• On page 10, plot 158-162 on the floor plan need to have their allocated colours displayed for that house type instead of grey. 158 and 160 to be is Brixworth colours. 159 Ecton colour, 161 Gayton colour. 162 Holcot colour.\n• On Page 10, the Sywell and Everdon needs removing. It might be worth adding in the house types for plot 158-162 to fill the pages? \n• On page 12, The Buckby house type, please add annotation outside the lounge/dining to say ‘Balcony’\n• On page 14, in the decoration section, please remove the word ‘white’ before gloss in the bullet point \n• On page 12, und